{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "SB87", "title": "Sales and Use Tax Law: consumer designation: all-volunteer fire departments.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["SalesandUseTaxLaw", "all-volunteerfiredepartments", "consumerdesignation"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing sales and use tax laws, among other things, impose a tax on retailers measured by the gross receipts from their sales of tangible personal property sold at retail in this state. The Sales and Use Tax Law makes certain sellers of tangible personal property consumers, and not retailers, of the tangible personal property they sell, including, until January 1, 2026, an all-volunteer fire department, as defined, if the profits are used solely and exclusively in furtherance of the purposes of the all-volunteer fire department, as prescribed.\n\nThis bill would extend the sunset described above until January 1, 2031.\n\nExisting law requires any bill authorizing a new tax expenditure to contain, among other things, specific goals, purposes, and objectives that the tax expenditure will achieve, detailed performance indicators, and data collection requirements.\n\nThe bill also would include additional information required for any bill authorizing a new tax expenditure.\n\nThe Bradley-Burns Uniform Local Sales and Use Tax Law authorizes counties and cities to impose local sales and use taxes in conformity with the Sales and Use Tax Law, and existing laws authorize districts, as specified, to impose transactions and use taxes in accordance with the Transactions and Use Tax Law, which generally conforms to the Sales and Use Tax Law. Amendments to the Sales and Use Tax Law are automatically incorporated into the local tax laws.\n\nExisting law requires the state to reimburse counties and cities for revenue losses caused by the enactment of sales and use tax exemptions.\n\nThis bill would provide that, notwithstanding Section 2230 of the Revenue and Taxation Code, no appropriation is made and the state shall not reimburse any local agencies for sales and use tax revenues lost by them pursuant to this bill.\n\nThis bill would take effect immediately as a tax levy."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. Read first time. To Com. on RLS. for assignment. To print.", "date": "2025-01-21", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["introduction", "reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be acted upon on or after February 21.", "date": "2025-01-22", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on REV. & TAX.", "date": "2025-01-29", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on REV. & TAX.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee with author's amendments. Read second time and amended. Re-referred to Com. on REV. & TAX.", "date": "2025-02-24", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["amendment-passage", "committee-passage", "reading-1", "reading-2", "referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on REV. & TAX.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "Set for hearing March 12.", "date": "2025-02-26", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From committee: Do pass and re-refer to Com. on APPR. with recommendation: To consent calendar. (Ayes 5. Noes 0.) (March 12). Re-referred to Com. on APPR.", "date": "2025-03-12", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["committee-passage", "committee-passage-favorable", "referral-committee"], "related_entities"